{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859049511,"sessionID":"ses_2868da312ffeM3OfRVFAF4u2oG","part":{"id":"prt_d79728eb4001jhtTAbptvlO7RC","messageID":"msg_d79728283001ELsJxJ4IRDsgYq","sessionID":"ses_2868da312ffeM3OfRVFAF4u2oG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a7fe4359a1d241afafe29df8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal implements the PicoD command execution API for the `pkg/picod` module in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Secure Command Execution** - Execute commands within controlled sandbox environments with proper isolation\n8: 2. **Resource Limit Enforcement** - Enforce CPU, memory, time, and output size limits on command execution\n9: 3. **Output Capture and Streaming** - Capture stdout/stderr with optional streaming for long-running commands\n10: 4. **Cancellation Support** - Enable command cancellation via context for graceful termination\n11: 5. **Security Hardening** - Implement security validations to prevent privilege escalation and command injection\n12: \n13: This implementation builds upon the sandbox infrastructure established in AR-012 and provides the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n14: \n15: ## Scope\n16: \n17: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n18: **Language:** Go  \n19: **Size:** M\n20: \n21: This AR covers:\n22: \n23: - **In scope:**\n24:   - Core `PicoD` struct and initialization (`picod.go`)\n25:   - Command execution logic with resource limits (`executor.go`)\n26:   - Resource limit configuration and enforcement (`limits.go`)\n27:   - Output capture and streaming (`output.go`)\n28:   - Security validations and sandboxing (`security.go`)\n29:   - Unit tests with mocked executors\n30:   - Integration tests with real command execution\n31:   - Configuration via environment variables\n32: \n33: - **Out of scope:**\n34:   - Container runtime integration (covered in AR-005, AR-009)\n35:   - Network namespace manipulation\n36:   - User namespace management\n37:   - Filesystem isolation beyond chroot/workspace jail\n38:   - Distributed command execution\n39:   - PicoD HTTP daemon (covered in `code-execution/` specs)\n40: \n41: ## Current State Analysis\n42: \n43: ### Existing Sandbox Infrastructure\n44: \n45: The current system has sandbox management infrastructure:\n46: \n47: 1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`):\n48:    - Creates and manages sandbox pods\n49:    - Handles lifecycle (create, update, delete)\n50:    - Supports warm pool for pre-provisioned sandboxes\n51: \n52: 2. **CodeInterpreter CRD** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`):\n53:    - Defines `CodeInterpreterSpec` with image, command, args, env, resources\n54:    - Supports `AuthMode` enum (`picod` or `none`)\n55:    - Default image: `volcanosh/picod:latest`\n56: \n57: 3. **Workload Manager**:\n58:    - Handles `CodeInterpreter` resources\n59:    - Creates underlying sandbox pods\n60:    - Injects `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` when `AuthMode=picod`\n61: \n62: ### Gaps Identified\n63: \n64: 1. **No unified execution API** - Command execution logic is scattered or non-existent\n65: 2. **No resource limit enforcement** - No programmatic way to enforce CPU/memory/time limits\n66: 3. **No output streaming** - Cannot stream output for long-running commands\n67: 4. **No security hardening** - Missing input validation and sandboxing at the API level\n68: 5. **No cancellation support** - Cannot gracefully cancel running commands\n69: \n70: ### PicoD Context\n71: \n72: Per `code-execution/design.md` and `code-execution/spec.md`:\n73: - PicoD is an HTTP daemon that runs commands inside a configurable workspace jail\n74: - Exposes health endpoint with JWT (RSA)-protected APIs\n75: - CLI flags: `-port` (default 8080), `-workspace` (default: current working directory)\n76: - Server uses `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds\n77: \n78: ## Proposed Changes\n79: \n80: ### 1. Core PicoD Structure (`picod.go`)\n81: \n82: ```go\n83: // PicoD represents a command execution sandbox\n84: type PicoD struct {\n85:     sandboxID    string\n86:     workDir      string\n87:     limits       *ResourceLimits\n88:     securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n89:     logger       klog.Logger\n90: }\n91: \n92: // Option is a functional option for PicoD\n93: type Option func(*PicoD)\n94: \n95: // New creates a new PicoD instance\n96: func New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD\n97: \n98: // WithWorkDir sets the working directory\n99: func WithWorkDir(dir string) Option\n100: \n101: // WithLimits sets resource limits\n102: func WithLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) Option\n103: \n104: // WithSecurityOpts sets security options\n105: func WithSecurityOpts(opts *SecurityOptions) Option\n106: \n107: // WithLogger sets the logger\n108: func WithLogger(logger klog.Logger) Option\n109: ```\n110: \n111: ### 2. Resource Limits (`limits.go`)\n112: \n113: ```go\n114: // ResourceLimits defines execution resource limits\n115: type ResourceLimits struct {\n116:     // Timeout is the maximum execution duration\n117:     Timeout time.Duration\n118:     \n119:     // MaxCPU is the maximum CPU cores (e.g., 0.5, 1.0)\n120:     MaxCPU float64\n121:     \n122:     // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes\n123:     MaxMemory int64\n124:     \n125:     // MaxOutputSize is the maximum output size in bytes\n126:     MaxOutputSize int64\n127:     \n128:     // MaxProcesses is the maximum number of processes\n129:     MaxProcesses int\n130: }\n131: \n132: // DefaultResourceLimits returns default resource limits\n133: func DefaultResourceLimits() *ResourceLimits\n134: \n135: // Validate validates resource limits\n136: func (l *ResourceLimits) Validate() error\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### 3. Security Options (`security.go`)\n140: \n141: ```go\n142: // SecurityOptions defines security settings for command execution\n143: type SecurityOptions struct {\n144:     // UID is the user ID to run commands as\n145:     UID int\n146:     \n147:     // GID is the group ID to run commands as\n148:     GID int\n149:     \n150:     // Capabilities is the list of allowed capabilities\n151:     Capabilities []string\n152:     \n153:     // ReadOnlyFS makes the filesystem read-only\n154:     ReadOnlyFS bool\n155:     \n156:     // NoNetwork disables network access\n157:     NoNetwork bool\n158:     \n159:     // AllowedCommands is an optional allowlist of command paths\n160:     AllowedCommands []string\n161: }\n162: \n163: // DefaultSecurityOpts returns default security options\n164: func DefaultSecurityOpts() *SecurityOptions\n165: \n166: // Validate validates security options\n167: func (o *SecurityOptions) Validate() error\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### 4. Command Execution API (`executor.go`)\n171: \n172: ```go\n173: // Command represents a command to execute\n174: type Command struct {\n175:     // Path is the command path\n176:     Path string\n177:     \n178:     // Args are the command arguments\n179:     Args []string\n180:     \n181:     // Env is the environment variables\n182:     Env []string\n183:     \n184:     // Dir is the working directory\n185:     Dir string\n186:     \n187:     // Stdin is the standard input\n188:     Stdin io.Reader\n189:     \n190:     // Stdout is the standard output (optional, captured if nil)\n191:     Stdout io.Writer\n192:     \n193:     // Stderr is the standard error (optional, captured if nil)\n194:     Stderr io.Writer\n195: }\n196: \n197: // CommandResult represents the result of command execution\n198: type CommandResult struct {\n199:     // ExitCode is the process exit code\n200:     ExitCode int\n201:     \n202:     // Stdout is the captured standard output\n203:     Stdout []byte\n204:     \n205:     // Stderr is the captured standard error\n206:     Stderr []byte\n207:     \n208:     // Duration is the execution duration\n209:     Duration time.Duration\n210:     \n211:     // OOMKilled indicates if the process was killed due to OOM\n212:     OOMKilled bool\n213:     \n214:     // Timeout indicates if the command timed out\n215:     Timeout bool\n216: }\n217: \n218: // Run executes a command and waits for completion\n219: func (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\n220: \n221: // Start starts a command without waiting\n222: func (p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\n223: \n224: // Process represents a running process\n225: type Process struct {\n226:     // PID is the process ID\n227:     PID int\n228:     \n229:     // Wait waits for the process to complete\n230:     Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\n231:     \n232:     // Kill sends a signal to the process\n233:     Kill(signal os.Signal) error\n234: }\n235: ```\n236: \n237: ### 5. Output Streaming (`output.go`)\n238: \n239: ```go\n240: // OutputHandler handles streaming output\n241: type OutputHandler interface {\n242:     // OnStdout is called when stdout data is available\n243:     OnStdout(data []byte)\n244:     \n245:     // OnStderr is called when stderr data is available\n246:     OnStderr(data []byte)\n247:     \n248:     // OnComplete is called when execution completes\n249:     OnComplete(result *CommandResult)\n250: }\n251: \n252: // RunWithStreaming executes a command with streaming output\n253: func (p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)\n254: ```\n255: \n256: ### 6. Security Validation (`security.go`)\n257: \n258: ```go\n259: // ValidateCommand validates a command for security\n260: func ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error\n261: \n262: // IsPathSafe checks if a path is within the allowed workspace\n263: func IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool\n264: \n265: // DropPrivileges drops privileges to the specified UID/GID\n266: func DropPrivileges(uid, gid int) error\n267: \n268: // SetResourceLimits applies resource limits to the current process\n269: func SetResourceLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) error\n270: ```\n271: \n272: ### 7. Configuration\n273: \n274: #### Environment Variables\n275: \n276: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n277: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n278: | `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n279: | `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n280: | `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n281: | `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n282: | `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Default output size limit |\n283: | `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES` | No | `10` | Default process limit |\n284: \n285: ### 8. Error Handling\n286: \n287: ```go\n288: // ExecutionError represents an execution error\n289: type ExecutionError struct {\n290:     // Type is the error type\n291:     Type ExecutionErrorType\n292:     \n293:     // Message is the error message\n294:     Message string\n295:     \n296:     // Underlying is the underlying error\n297:     Underlying error\n298: }\n299: \n300: type ExecutionErrorType string\n301: \n302: const (\n303:     ExecutionErrorTimeout    ExecutionErrorType = \"timeout\"\n304:     ExecutionErrorOOM        ExecutionErrorType = \"oom\"\n305:     ExecutionErrorCancelled  ExecutionErrorType = \"cancelled\"\n306:     ExecutionErrorSecurity   ExecutionErrorType = \"security\"\n307:     ExecutionErrorResource   ExecutionErrorType = \"resource\"\n308:     ExecutionErrorExec       ExecutionErrorType = \"exec\"\n309: )\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ## Impact Analysis\n313: \n314: ### Dependencies\n315: \n316: | Package | Purpose |\n317: |---------|---------|\n318: | `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n319: | `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n320: | `syscall` | Process management and signals |\n321: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n322: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type definitions |\n323: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Type definitions |\n324: \n325: ### Affected Components\n326: \n327: 1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`): Will use PicoD for command execution within sandboxes\n328: 2. **Workload Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`): Will invoke PicoD APIs for job execution\n329: 3. **Code Interpreter** (standalone daemon): Will use PicoD execution logic\n330: 4. **Security Module**: Will configure security policies for command execution\n331: 5. **Monitoring System**: Will collect metrics from command execution\n332: \n333: ### Backward Compatibility\n334: \n335: - This is a new module with no existing API surface\n336: - No breaking changes to existing components\n337: - Configuration via environment variables and programmatic API\n338: - Existing `CodeInterpreter` CRD already references PicoD image\n339: \n340: ### Risk Assessment\n341: \n342: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n343: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n344: | Command injection | Low | High | Input validation, allowlist-based command selection |\n345: | Resource exhaustion | Medium | High | Enforce strict CPU/memory/time limits |\n346: | Privilege escalation | Low | Critical | Run as non-root, drop capabilities, use namespaces |\n347: | Output buffer overflow | Low | Medium | Stream large outputs, enforce size limits |\n348: | Zombie processes | Medium | Low | Proper process reaping, signal handling |\n349: \n350: ## Alternatives Considered\n351: \n352: ### Alternative 1: Use Existing Library (e.g., go-execute, bazel-remote)\n353: \n354: **Approach**: Leverage existing command execution libraries\n355: \n356: **Pros**:\n357: - Less code to maintain\n358: - Battle-tested implementations\n359: - Community support\n360: \n361: **Cons**:\n362: - May not meet specific security requirements for sandboxed execution\n363: - Additional dependency management overhead\n364: - Less control over resource limit enforcement\n365: - May not support Kubernetes-native patterns\n366: \n367: **Decision**: Implement custom solution for full control over security and limits, and better integration with AgentCube architecture.\n368: \n369: ### Alternative 2: Shell-based Execution\n370: \n371: **Approach**: Execute commands via `/bin/sh -c`\n372: \n373: **Pros**:\n374: - Simple implementation\n375: - Shell features (pipes, redirection) available\n376: - Familiar syntax\n377: \n378: **Cons**:\n379: - Security risks (shell injection attacks)\n380: - Harder to control resource limits accurately\n381: - Additional attack surface\n382: - Non-deterministic behavior across shells\n383: \n384: **Decision**: Use direct execve-style execution for better security and control.\n385: \n386: ### Alternative 3: Container-based Execution\n387: \n388: **Approach**: Spawn a new container for each command\n389: \n390: **Pros**:\n391: - Strong isolation\n392: - Built-in resource limits via cgroups\n393: - Clean environment per command\n394: \n395: **Cons**:\n396: - High overhead (container startup latency)\n397: - Requires container runtime access\n398: - Complex orchestration\n399: - Overkill for simple command execution\n400: \n401: **Decision**: Use process-level isolation with proper limits for lower latency; container isolation is handled at the sandbox pod level (AR-005).\n402: \n403: ## Testing Strategy\n404: \n405: ### Unit Tests\n406: \n407: 1. **TestPicoD_Run_Success**: Basic command execution\n408: 2. **TestPicoD_Run_Timeout**: Command exceeds timeout\n409: 3. **TestPicoD_Run_OOM**: Command exceeds memory limit\n410: 4. **TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled**: Context cancellation\n411: 5. **TestPicoD_OutputCapture**: Stdout/stderr capture\n412: 6. **TestPicoD_SecurityValidation**: Invalid commands rejected\n413: 7. **TestPicoD_ResourceLimits_Validate**: Resource limit validation\n414: 8. **TestPicoD_SecurityOpts_Validate**: Security options validation\n415: 9. **TestPicoD_WithOptions**: Functional options pattern\n416: 10. **TestPicoD_ExecutionErrorTypes**: Error type classification\n417: \n418: ### Integration Tests\n419: \n420: 1. **TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle**: Full execution flow\n421: 2. **TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent**: Multiple concurrent commands\n422: 3. **TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits**: Verify limits are enforced\n423: 4. **TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming**: Output streaming functionality\n424: 5. **TestPicoD_Integration_SignalHandling**: Process signal handling\n425: \n426: ## Acceptance Criteria\n427: \n428: - [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n429: - [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n430: - [ ] Output capture works correctly (stdout, stderr, exit code)\n431: - [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n432: - [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n433: - [ ] Streaming output is supported\n434: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n435: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n436: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n437: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n438: - [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n439: \n440: ## References\n441: \n442: - Sandbox Infrastructure: `changes/AR-012/proposal.md`\n443: - Session Storage: `changes/AR-013/proposal.md`\n444: - Valkey Storage: `changes/AR-014/proposal.md`\n445: - PicoD Spec: `code-execution/spec.md`\n446: - PicoD Design: `code-execution/design.md`\n447: - Client-Go: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 447 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the PicoD command execution API for the `pkg/picod` module in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Secure Command Execution** - Execute commands within controlled sandbox environments with proper isolation\n2. **Resource Limit Enforcement** - Enforce CPU, memory, time, and output size limits on command execution\n3. **Output Capture and Streaming** - Capture stdout/stderr with optional streaming for long-running commands\n4. **Cancellation Support** - Enable command cancellation via context for graceful termination\n5. **Security Hardening** - Implement security validations to prevent privilege escalation and command injection\n\nThis implementation builds upon the sandbox infrastructure established in AR-012 and provides the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/AR-015-proposal.md","time":{"start":1775859049480,"end":1775859049509}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859049518,"sessionID":"ses_2868da312ffeM3OfRVFAF4u2oG","part":{"id":"prt_d797293c2001yHmu2Zx8xN4aTn","messageID":"msg_d79728283001ELsJxJ4IRDsgYq","sessionID":"ses_2868da312ffeM3OfRVFAF4u2oG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5ad4073fc4484ec88c34c266","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-015 PicoD Command Execution API\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 completed |\n12: \n13: This document describes the technical implementation for the PicoD command execution API within `pkg/picod`. The PicoD module provides secure, resource-limited command execution capabilities for the AgentCube platform, serving as the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n14: \n15: ## Architecture\n16: \n17: ### Component Structure\n18: \n19: ```\n20: pkg/picod/\n21: ├── picod.go                 # Main PicoD struct and initialization\n22: ├── picod_test.go            # PicoD unit tests\n23: ├── executor.go              # Command execution logic\n24: ├── executor_test.go         # Execution unit tests\n25: ├── limits.go                # Resource limit definitions and enforcement\n26: ├── limits_test.go           # Resource limit tests\n27: ├── security.go              # Security validation and hardening\n28: ├── security_test.go         # Security tests\n29: ├── output.go                # Output capture and streaming\n30: ├── output_test.go           # Output handling tests\n31: ├── process.go               # Running process management\n32: ├── process_test.go          # Process management tests\n33: ├── errors.go                # Error type definitions\n34: └── config.go                # Configuration from environment\n35: ```\n36: \n37: ### Integration Points\n38: \n39: - **os/exec**: Standard library command execution primitives\n40: - **syscall**: Process management, signals, and resource limits\n41: - **context**: Command cancellation and timeouts\n42: - **k8s.io/klog/v2**: Structured logging\n43: - **pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1**: Type definitions for CodeInterpreter\n44: - **pkg/common/types**: SandboxInfo type definitions\n45: \n46: ### Execution Flow\n47: \n48: ```\n49: Client (WorkloadManager/CodeInterpreter)\n50:   ↓\n51: PicoD.New(sandboxID, options...)\n52:   ↓\n53: PicoD.Run(ctx, Command)\n54:   ├─ ValidateCommand(cmd, securityOpts)\n55:   ├─ ApplyResourceLimits(limits)\n56:   ├─ exec.CommandContext(ctx, path, args...)\n57:   ├─ Configure cmd.SysProcAttr\n58:   ├─ Start process\n59:   ├─ Monitor with timeout/limits\n60:   ├─ Capture stdout/stderr\n61:   └─ Return CommandResult\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ## Data Structures\n65: \n66: ### PicoD\n67: \n68: ```go\n69: // PicoD represents a command execution sandbox\n70: type PicoD struct {\n71:     sandboxID    string\n72:     workDir      string\n73:     limits       *ResourceLimits\n74:     securityOpts *SecurityOptions\n75:     logger       klog.Logger\n76: }\n77: \n78: // Option is a functional option for PicoD\n79: type Option func(*PicoD)\n80: ```\n81: \n82: ### ResourceLimits\n83: \n84: ```go\n85: // ResourceLimits defines execution resource limits\n86: type ResourceLimits struct {\n87:     // Timeout is the maximum execution duration\n88:     Timeout time.Duration\n89:     \n90:     // MaxCPU is the maximum CPU cores (e.g., 0.5, 1.0)\n91:     MaxCPU float64\n92:     \n93:     // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes\n94:     MaxMemory int64\n95:     \n96:     // MaxOutputSize is the maximum output size in bytes\n97:     MaxOutputSize int64\n98:     \n99:     // MaxProcesses is the maximum number of processes\n100:     MaxProcesses int\n101: }\n102: ```\n103: \n104: ### SecurityOptions\n105: \n106: ```go\n107: // SecurityOptions defines security settings for command execution\n108: type SecurityOptions struct {\n109:     // UID is the user ID to run commands as\n110:     UID int\n111:     \n112:     // GID is the group ID to run commands as\n113:     GID int\n114:     \n115:     // Capabilities is the list of allowed capabilities\n116:     Capabilities []string\n117:     \n118:     // ReadOnlyFS makes the filesystem read-only\n119:     ReadOnlyFS bool\n120:     \n121:     // NoNetwork disables network access\n122:     NoNetwork bool\n123:     \n124:     // AllowedCommands is an optional allowlist of command paths\n125:     AllowedCommands []string\n126: }\n127: ```\n128: \n129: ### Command\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: // Command represents a command to execute\n133: type Command struct {\n134:     // Path is the command path\n135:     Path string\n136:     \n137:     // Args are the command arguments\n138:     Args []string\n139:     \n140:     // Env is the environment variables\n141:     Env []string\n142:     \n143:     // Dir is the working directory\n144:     Dir string\n145:     \n146:     // Stdin is the standard input\n147:     Stdin io.Reader\n148:     \n149:     // Stdout is the standard output (optional, captured if nil)\n150:     Stdout io.Writer\n151:     \n152:     // Stderr is the standard error (optional, captured if nil)\n153:     Stderr io.Writer\n154: }\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### CommandResult\n158: \n159: ```go\n160: // CommandResult represents the result of command execution\n161: type CommandResult struct {\n162:     // ExitCode is the process exit code\n163:     ExitCode int\n164:     \n165:     // Stdout is the captured standard output\n166:     Stdout []byte\n167:     \n168:     // Stderr is the captured standard error\n169:     Stderr []byte\n170:     \n171:     // Duration is the execution duration\n172:     Duration time.Duration\n173:     \n174:     // OOMKilled indicates if the process was killed due to OOM\n175:     OOMKilled bool\n176:     \n177:     // Timeout indicates if the command timed out\n178:     Timeout bool\n179: }\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ### Process\n183: \n184: ```go\n185: // Process represents a running process\n186: type Process struct {\n187:     // PID is the process ID\n188:     PID int\n189:     \n190:     // cmd is the underlying exec.Cmd\n191:     cmd *exec.Cmd\n192:     \n193:     // startTime is when the process started\n194:     startTime time.Time\n195: }\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### OutputHandler\n199: \n200: ```go\n201: // OutputHandler handles streaming output\n202: type OutputHandler interface {\n203:     // OnStdout is called when stdout data is available\n204:     OnStdout(data []byte)\n205:     \n206:     // OnStderr is called when stderr data is available\n207:     OnStderr(data []byte)\n208:     \n209:     // OnComplete is called when execution completes\n210:     OnComplete(result *CommandResult)\n211: }\n212: ```\n213: \n214: ## API Contracts\n215: \n216: ### PicoD Initialization\n217: \n218: ```go\n219: // New creates a new PicoD instance\n220: func New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD\n221: \n222: // WithWorkDir sets the working directory\n223: func WithWorkDir(dir string) Option\n224: \n225: // WithLimits sets resource limits\n226: func WithLimits(limits *ResourceLimits) Option\n227: \n228: // WithSecurityOpts sets security options\n229: func WithSecurityOpts(opts *SecurityOptions) Option\n230: \n231: // WithLogger sets the logger\n232: func WithLogger(logger klog.Logger) Option\n233: ```\n234: \n235: ### Command Execution\n236: \n237: ```go\n238: // Run executes a command and waits for completion\n239: func (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error)\n240: \n241: // Start starts a command without waiting\n242: func (p *PicoD) Start(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*Process, error)\n243: \n244: // RunWithStreaming executes a command with streaming output\n245: func (p *PicoD) RunWithStreaming(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command, handler OutputHandler) (*CommandResult, error)\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ### Process Management\n249: \n250: ```go\n251: // Wait waits for the process to complete\n252: func (p *Process) Wait() (*CommandResult, error)\n253: \n254: // Kill sends a signal to the process\n255: func (p *Process) Kill(signal os.Signal) error\n256: \n257: // Signal sends a specific signal to the process\n258: func (p *Process) Signal(sig syscall.Signal) error\n259: ```\n260: \n261: ### Resource Limits\n262: \n263: ```go\n264: // DefaultResourceLimits returns default resource limits\n265: func DefaultResourceLimits() *ResourceLimits\n266: \n267: // Validate validates resource limits\n268: func (l *ResourceLimits) Validate() error\n269: \n270: // Apply applies resource limits to a process\n271: func (l *ResourceLimits) Apply(cmd *exec.Cmd) error\n272: ```\n273: \n274: ### Security Validation\n275: \n276: ```go\n277: // DefaultSecurityOpts returns default security options\n278: func DefaultSecurityOpts() *SecurityOptions\n279: \n280: // Validate validates security options\n281: func (o *SecurityOptions) Validate() error\n282: \n283: // ValidateCommand validates a command for security\n284: func ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error\n285: \n286: // IsPathSafe checks if a path is within the allowed workspace\n287: func IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool\n288: ```\n289: \n290: ### Configuration\n291: \n292: ```go\n293: // LoadConfig loads configuration from environment variables\n294: func LoadConfig() (*Config, error)\n295: \n296: // Config holds PicoD configuration\n297: type Config struct {\n298:     WorkDir         string\n299:     DefaultTimeout  time.Duration\n300:     MaxMemory       int64\n301:     MaxCPU          float64\n302:     MaxOutputSize   int64\n303:     MaxProcesses    int\n304: }\n305: ```\n306: \n307: ## Error Handling\n308: \n309: ### ExecutionError\n310: \n311: ```go\n312: // ExecutionError represents an execution error\n313: type ExecutionError struct {\n314:     // Type is the error type\n315:     Type ExecutionErrorType\n316:     \n317:     // Message is the error message\n318:     Message string\n319:     \n320:     // Underlying is the underlying error\n321:     Underlying error\n322: }\n323: \n324: // Error implements the error interface\n325: func (e *ExecutionError) Error() string\n326: \n327: // Unwrap returns the underlying error\n328: func (e *ExecutionError) Unwrap() error\n329: ```\n330: \n331: ### ExecutionErrorType\n332: \n333: ```go\n334: type ExecutionErrorType string\n335: \n336: const (\n337:     ExecutionErrorTimeout    ExecutionErrorType = \"timeout\"\n338:     ExecutionErrorOOM        ExecutionErrorType = \"oom\"\n339:     ExecutionErrorCancelled  ExecutionErrorType = \"cancelled\"\n340:     ExecutionErrorSecurity   ExecutionErrorType = \"security\"\n341:     ExecutionErrorResource   ExecutionErrorType = \"resource\"\n342:     ExecutionErrorExec       ExecutionErrorType = \"exec\"\n343: )\n344: ```\n345: \n346: ### Error Conditions\n347: \n348: | Condition | Error Type | HTTP Mapping | Description |\n349: |-----------|------------|--------------|-------------|\n350: | Command exceeds timeout | `ExecutionErrorTimeout` | 408 Request Timeout | Command execution exceeded configured timeout |\n351: | Command exceeds memory | `ExecutionErrorOOM` | 413 Payload Too Large | Process was killed due to OOM |\n352: | Context cancelled | `ExecutionErrorCancelled` | 499 Client Closed Request | Client cancelled the operation |\n353: | Security violation | `ExecutionErrorSecurity` | 403 Forbidden | Command failed security validation |\n354: | Resource limit invalid | `ExecutionErrorResource` | 400 Bad Request | Invalid resource limit configuration |\n355: | Exec failure | `ExecutionErrorExec` | 500 Internal Server Error | Failed to start/execute command |\n356: \n357: ## Implementation Details\n358: \n359: ### PicoD Initialization\n360: \n361: ```go\n362: func New(sandboxID string, opts ...Option) *PicoD {\n363:     p := &PicoD{\n364:         sandboxID:    sandboxID,\n365:         workDir:      \"/tmp/picod/\" + sandboxID,\n366:         limits:       DefaultResourceLimits(),\n367:         securityOpts: DefaultSecurityOpts(),\n368:         logger:       klog.Background(),\n369:     }\n370:     \n371:     for _, opt := range opts {\n372:         opt(p)\n373:     }\n374:     \n375:     return p\n376: }\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ### Command Execution Flow\n380: \n381: ```go\n382: func (p *PicoD) Run(ctx context.Context, cmd *Command) (*CommandResult, error) {\n383:     // 1. Validate command\n384:     if err := ValidateCommand(cmd, p.securityOpts); err != nil {\n385:         return nil, &ExecutionError{\n386:             Type:    ExecutionErrorSecurity,\n387:             Message: \"command validation failed\",\n388:             Underlying: err,\n389:         }\n390:     }\n391:     \n392:     // 2. Create exec.Cmd\n393:     execCmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, cmd.Path, cmd.Args...)\n394:     \n395:     // 3. Configure environment\n396:     execCmd.Env = cmd.Env\n397:     execCmd.Dir = cmd.Dir\n398:     \n399:     // 4. Apply resource limits\n400:     if err := p.limits.Apply(execCmd); err != nil {\n401:         return nil, &ExecutionError{\n402:             Type:    ExecutionErrorResource,\n403:             Message: \"failed to apply resource limits\",\n404:             Underlying: err,\n405:         }\n406:     }\n407:     \n408:     // 5. Capture output\n409:     var stdoutBuf, stderrBuf bytes.Buffer\n410:     if cmd.Stdout == nil {\n411:         execCmd.Stdout = &stdoutBuf\n412:     } else {\n413:         execCmd.Stdout = cmd.Stdout\n414:     }\n415:     if cmd.Stderr == nil {\n416:         execCmd.Stderr = &stderrBuf\n417:     } else {\n418:         execCmd.Stderr = cmd.Stderr\n419:     }\n420:     \n421:     // 6. Start execution\n422:     startTime := time.Now()\n423:     if err := execCmd.Start(); err != nil {\n424:         return nil, &ExecutionError{\n425:             Type:    ExecutionErrorExec,\n426:             Message: \"failed to start command\",\n427:             Underlying: err,\n428:         }\n429:     }\n430:     \n431:     // 7. Wait for completion\n432:     err := execCmd.Wait()\n433:     duration := time.Since(startTime)\n434:     \n435:     // 8. Build result\n436:     result := &CommandResult{\n437:         Duration: duration,\n438:     }\n439:     \n440:     if cmd.Stdout == nil {\n441:         result.Stdout = stdoutBuf.Bytes()\n442:     }\n443:     if cmd.Stderr == nil {\n444:         result.Stderr = stderrBuf.Bytes()\n445:     }\n446:     \n447:     // 9. Check for timeout/OOM\n448:     if ctx.Err() == context.DeadlineExceeded {\n449:         result.Timeout = true\n450:         err = &ExecutionError{\n451:             Type:    ExecutionErrorTimeout,\n452:             Message: \"command timed out\",\n453:         }\n454:     }\n455:     \n456:     if exitErr, ok := err.(*exec.ExitError); ok {\n457:         if status, ok := exitErr.Sys().(syscall.WaitStatus); ok {\n458:             if status.Signal() == syscall.SIGKILL {\n459:                 result.OOMKilled = true\n460:                 err = &ExecutionError{\n461:                     Type:    ExecutionErrorOOM,\n462:                     Message: \"process killed due to OOM\",\n463:                 }\n464:             }\n465:         }\n466:         result.ExitCode = exitErr.ExitCode()\n467:     } else if err == nil {\n468:         result.ExitCode = 0\n469:     }\n470:     \n471:     return result, err\n472: }\n473: ```\n474: \n475: ### Resource Limit Enforcement\n476: \n477: ```go\n478: func (l *ResourceLimits) Apply(cmd *exec.Cmd) error {\n479:     if cmd.SysProcAttr == nil {\n480:         cmd.SysProcAttr = &syscall.SysProcAttr{}\n481:     }\n482:     \n483:     // Set CPU limits via cgroups (Linux)\n484:     if l.MaxCPU > 0 {\n485:         // Use cpu.cfs_quota_us and cpu.cfs_period_us\n486:         // This requires cgroup setup\n487:     }\n488:     \n489:     // Set memory limits\n490:     if l.MaxMemory > 0 {\n491:         cmd.SysProcAttr.Setpgid = true\n492:         // Memory limits via setrlimit\n493:         syscall.Setrlimit(syscall.RLIMIT_AS, &syscall.Rlimit{\n494:             Cur: uint64(l.MaxMemory),\n495:             Max: uint64(l.MaxMemory),\n496:         })\n497:     }\n498:     \n499:     // Set process limits\n500:     if l.MaxProcesses > 0 {\n501:         syscall.Setrlimit(syscall.RLIMIT_NPROC, &syscall.Rlimit{\n502:             Cur: uint64(l.MaxProcesses),\n503:             Max: uint64(l.MaxProcesses),\n504:         })\n505:     }\n506:     \n507:     return nil\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ### Security Validation\n512: \n513: ```go\n514: func ValidateCommand(cmd *Command, opts *SecurityOptions) error {\n515:     // 1. Check if command path is in allowlist\n516:     if len(opts.AllowedCommands) > 0 {\n517:         allowed := false\n518:         for _, allowedCmd := range opts.AllowedCommands {\n519:             if cmd.Path == allowedCmd {\n520:                 allowed = true\n521:                 break\n522:             }\n523:         }\n524:         if !allowed {\n525:             return fmt.Errorf(\"command %q not in allowlist\", cmd.Path)\n526:         }\n527:     }\n528:     \n529:     // 2. Validate working directory\n530:     if cmd.Dir != \"\" && !IsPathSafe(cmd.Dir, opts.WorkDir) {\n531:         return fmt.Errorf(\"working directory %q is outside workspace\", cmd.Dir)\n532:     }\n533:     \n534:     // 3. Check for path traversal in arguments\n535:     for _, arg := range cmd.Args {\n536:         if strings.Contains(arg, \"..\") {\n537:             return fmt.Errorf(\"argument %q contains path traversal\", arg)\n538:         }\n539:     }\n540:     \n541:     // 4. Validate environment variables\n542:     for _, env := range cmd.Env {\n543:         if strings.HasPrefix(env, \"LD_PRELOAD\") || strings.HasPrefix(env, \"LD_LIBRARY_PATH\") {\n544:             return fmt.Errorf(\"dangerous environment variable: %s\", env)\n545:         }\n546:     }\n547:     \n548:     return nil\n549: }\n550: \n551: func IsPathSafe(path, workDir string) bool {\n552:     absPath, err := filepath.Abs(path)\n553:     if err != nil {\n554:         return false\n555:     }\n556:     \n557:     absWorkDir, err := filepath.Abs(workDir)\n558:     if err != nil {\n559:         return false\n560:     }\n561:     \n562:     return strings.HasPrefix(absPath, absWorkDir)\n563: }\n564: ```\n565: \n566: ## Configuration\n567: \n568: ### Environment Variables\n569: \n570: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n571: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n572: | `PICOD_WORKDIR` | No | `/tmp/picod` | Base working directory |\n573: | `PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | No | `30s` | Default command timeout |\n574: | `PICOD_MAX_MEMORY` | No | `128Mi` | Default memory limit |\n575: | `PICOD_MAX_CPU` | No | `1.0` | Default CPU limit |\n576: | `PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE` | No | `10MB` | Default output size limit |\n577: | `PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES` | No | `10` | Default process limit |\n578: \n579: ### Example Configuration\n580: \n581: ```go\n582: config := &Config{\n583:     WorkDir:        \"/tmp/picod\",\n584:     DefaultTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n585:     MaxMemory:      128 * 1024 * 1024, // 128 MiB\n586:     MaxCPU:         1.0,\n587:     MaxOutputSize:  10 * 1024 * 1024, // 10 MiB\n588:     MaxProcesses:   10,\n589: }\n590: ```\n591: \n592: ## Testing Strategy\n593: \n594: ### Unit Tests\n595: \n596: | Test | Purpose |\n597: |------|---------|\n598: | `TestPicoD_Run_Success` | Basic command execution |\n599: | `TestPicoD_Run_Timeout` | Command exceeds timeout |\n600: | `TestPicoD_Run_OOM` | Command exceeds memory limit |\n601: | `TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled` | Context cancellation |\n602: | `TestPicoD_OutputCapture` | Stdout/stderr capture |\n603: | `TestPicoD_SecurityValidation` | Invalid commands rejected |\n604: | `TestPicoD_ResourceLimits_Validate` | Resource limit validation |\n605: | `TestPicoD_SecurityOpts_Validate` | Security options validation |\n606: | `TestPicoD_WithOptions` | Functional options pattern |\n607: | `TestPicoD_ExecutionErrorTypes` | Error type classification |\n608: \n609: ### Integration Tests\n610: \n611: | Test | Purpose |\n612: |------|---------|\n613: | `TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle` | Full execution flow |\n614: | `TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent` | Multiple concurrent commands |\n615: | `TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits` | Verify limits are enforced |\n616: | `TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming` | Output streaming functionality |\n617: | `TestPicoD_Integration_SignalHandling` | Process signal handling |\n618: \n619: ### Test Fixtures\n620: \n621: ```go\n622: // mockOutputHandler implements OutputHandler for testing\n623: type mockOutputHandler struct {\n624:     stdoutCalls [][]byte\n625:     stderrCalls [][]byte\n626:     completeCalled bool\n627:     lastResult *CommandResult\n628: }\n629: \n630: func (m *mockOutputHandler) OnStdout(data []byte) {\n631:     m.stdoutCalls = append(m.stdoutCalls, data)\n632: }\n633: \n634: func (m *mockOutputHandler) OnStderr(data []byte) {\n635:     m.stderrCalls = append(m.stderrCalls, data)\n636: }\n637: \n638: func (m *mockOutputHandler) OnComplete(result *CommandResult) {\n639:     m.completeCalled = true\n640:     m.lastResult = result\n641: }\n642: ```\n643: \n644: ## Acceptance Criteria\n645: \n646: - [ ] `PicoD` struct implements all required methods\n647: - [ ] Resource limits are enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n648: - [ ] Output capture works correctly (stdout, stderr, exit code)\n649: - [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n650: - [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n651: - [ ] Streaming output is supported\n652: - [ ] All unit tests pass\n653: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n654: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n655: - [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n656: - [ ] Error types are properly classified and documented\n657: \n658: ## Dependencies\n659: \n660: | Package | Purpose |\n661: |---------|---------|\n662: | `context` | Command cancellation and timeouts |\n663: | `os/exec` | Command execution primitives |\n664: | `syscall` | Process management and signals |\n665: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging |\n666: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo type definitions |\n667: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Type definitions |\n668: \n669: ## Affected Components\n670: \n671: 1. **Sandbox Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox/`): Will use PicoD for command execution within sandboxes\n672: 2. **Workload Manager** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`): Will invoke PicoD APIs for job execution\n673: 3. **Code Interpreter** (standalone daemon): Will use PicoD execution logic\n674: 4. **Security Module**: Will configure security policies for command execution\n675: 5. **Monitoring System**: Will collect metrics from command execution\n676: \n677: ## References\n678: \n679: - AR-012: Sandbox Infrastructure\n680: - AR-013: Session Storage\n681: - AR-014: Valkey Storage\n682: - `code-execution/spec.md`: PicoD Specification\n683: - `code-execution/design.md`: PicoD Design\n684: - `deployment/client-go.md`: Kubernetes Client-Go\n\n(End of file - total 684 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-015 PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 completed |\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the PicoD command execution API within `pkg/picod`. The PicoD module provides secure, resource-limited command execution capabilities for the AgentCube platform, serving as the execution engine for code interpreters and agent runtimes.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/design.md","time":{"start":1775859049484,"end":1775859049516}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859049520,"sessionID":"ses_2868da312ffeM3OfRVFAF4u2oG","part":{"id":"prt_d79729eee001o7bITDKqyR5Grl","messageID":"msg_d79728283001ELsJxJ4IRDsgYq","sessionID":"ses_2868da312ffeM3OfRVFAF4u2oG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_46f82c19082b486c96d89912","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/apis  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Scaffold & Registration\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/` directory structure\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/register.go` - register API group\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/register.go` - define `SchemeGroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme`\n15: - [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/doc.go` - add Go package documentation\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Phase 2: Type Definitions\n20: \n21: - [ ] **2.1** Define `CodeInterpreterPhase` enum (Pending, Running, Failed, Terminating)\n22: - [ ] **2.2** Define `CodeInterpreterCondition` struct (type, status, reason, message, lastTransitionTime)\n23: - [ ] **2.3** Define `KernelSpec` struct (language, image, resources)\n24: - [ ] **2.4** Define `SessionConfig` struct (timeout, idleTimeout, maxSessions)\n25: - [ ] **2.5** Define `SecurityPolicy` struct (allowedPackages, blockedOperations, networkAccess)\n26: - [ ] **2.6** Define `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct (kernel, session, security, resources)\n27: - [ ] **2.7** Define `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct (phase, conditions, activeSessions, startTime, lastTransitionTime)\n28: - [ ] **2.8** Define `CodeInterpreter` struct (TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, Spec, Status)\n29: - [ ] **2.9** Define `CodeInterpreterList` struct (TypeMeta, ListMeta, Items)\n30: - [ ] **2.10** Add JSON tags (camelCase) and protobuf tags to all types\n31: - [ ] **2.11** Implement `runtime.Object` interface for CodeInterpreter and CodeInterpreterList\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## Phase 3: Defaults & Validation\n36: \n37: - [ ] **3.1** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/defaults.go`\n38: - [ ] **3.2** Implement `SetDefaults_CodeInterpreter` - set default phase to Pending, default kernel settings\n39: - [ ] **3.3** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/validation.go`\n40: - [ ] **3.4** Implement `ValidateCodeInterpreter` - validate spec fields (kernel language, resource values, security policies)\n41: - [ ] **3.5** Implement `ValidateCodeInterpreterStatusUpdate` - validate status transitions and field immutability\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Phase 4: CRD Manifest Generation\n46: \n47: - [ ] **4.1** Add `+genclient` and `+k8s:deepcopy-gen` markers to type definitions\n48: - [ ] **4.2** Add `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` and `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` markers\n49: - [ ] **4.3** Add `+kubebuilder:printcolumn` markers for kubectl output (NAME, PHASE, KERNEL, AGE)\n50: - [ ] **4.4** Run `make gen-crd` (controller-gen) to generate CRD YAML\n51: - [ ] **4.5** Verify generated manifest at `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml`\n52: - [ ] **4.6** Validate OpenAPI v3 schema in generated CRD\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## Phase 5: Client Code Generation\n57: \n58: - [ ] **5.1** Update `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` if needed\n59: - [ ] **5.2** Update `hack/update-codegen.sh` with API group info\n60: - [ ] **5.3** Run `make gen-client` to generate clientset, listers, informers\n61: - [ ] **5.4** Verify generated code compiles: `pkg/client/clientset/versioned/`\n62: - [ ] **5.5** Verify generated code compiles: `pkg/client/listers/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/`\n63: - [ ] **5.6** Verify generated code compiles: `pkg/client/informers/externalversions/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/`\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## Phase 6: Unit Tests\n68: \n69: - [ ] **6.1** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/types_test.go`\n70: - [ ] **6.2** Test type round-trip serialization (Go → JSON → Go)\n71: - [ ] **6.3** Test `SetDefaults_CodeInterpreter` behavior\n72: - [ ] **6.4** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/validation_test.go`\n73: - [ ] **6.5** Test valid CodeInterpreter specs pass validation\n74: - [ ] **6.6** Test invalid specs fail validation (unsupported languages, negative resources)\n75: - [ ] **6.7** Test status update validation (phase transitions, immutable fields)\n76: - [ ] **6.8** Test `AddToScheme` registration works correctly\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## Phase 7: Integration & Verification\n81: \n82: - [ ] **7.1** Run `make test` - all unit tests pass\n83: - [ ] **7.2** Run `make verify` - code generation is up to date\n84: - [ ] **7.3** Apply CRD to test cluster: `kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml`\n85: - [ ] **7.4** Verify `kubectl get codeinterpreter` shows custom columns\n86: - [ ] **7.5** Create sample CodeInterpreter YAML in `examples/codeinterpreter.yaml`\n87: - [ ] **7.6** Apply sample and verify resource is created\n88: - [ ] **7.7** Verify Go client can create/get/update CodeInterpreter resources\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## Verification Checklist\n93: \n94: - [ ] All Go code compiles without errors\n95: - [ ] `go test ./pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/...` passes with ≥80% coverage\n96: - [ ] CRD manifest validates with `kubeval` or `kubectl --dry-run=server`\n97: - [ ] Generated client code is up to date (`git diff` shows no changes after `make gen-client`)\n98: - [ ] Example YAML applies successfully to test cluster\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Dependencies\n103: \n104: | Task | Depends On |\n105: |------|------------|\n106: | Phase 2 | Phase 1 |\n107: | Phase 3 | Phase 2 |\n108: | Phase 4 | Phase 2 |\n109: | Phase 5 | Phase 4 |\n110: | Phase 6 | Phase 2, 3 |\n111: | Phase 7 | Phase 4, 5, 6 |\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ## References\n116: \n117: - Proposal: `changes/AR-002/proposal.md`\n118: - Implementation Plan: `proposal.md#implementation-plan`\n119: - Success Criteria: `proposal.md#success-criteria`\n120: - API Conventions: `https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md`\n121: - Related: `changes/AR-001/` (AgentRuntime CRD)\n\n(End of file - total 121 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/apis  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Scaffold & Registration\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/` directory structure\n- [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/register.go` - register API group\n- [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/register.go` - define `SchemeGroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme`\n- [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/apis/codeinterpreter/v1alpha1/doc.go` - add Go package documentation\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Type Definitions\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-002/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775859049489,"end":1775859049519}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859049523,"sessionID":"ses_2868da312ffeM3OfRVFAF4u2oG","part":{"id":"prt_d797298e100142dBMokPhfyEgG","messageID":"msg_d79728283001ELsJxJ4IRDsgYq","sessionID":"ses_2868da312ffeM3OfRVFAF4u2oG","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4d9c3f90dbda4e6ea0bb139b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `CreateSandboxRequest` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n18:   - Fields: `Kind`, `Name`, `Namespace` (all string)\n19:   - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n20:   - Validation rules: Kind ∈ {AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter}, Namespace non-empty, Name non-empty\n21: \n22: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `CreateSandboxResponse` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n23:   - Fields: `SessionID`, `SandboxID`, `SandboxName` (string), `EntryPoints` ([]SandboxEntryPoint)\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `SandboxEntryPoint` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n26:   - Fields: `Path`, `Protocol`, `Endpoint` (all string)\n27: \n28: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define context keys in `pkg/workloadmanager/auth.go`\n29:   - Keys: `contextKeyUserToken`, `contextKeyServiceAccount`, `contextKeyServiceAccountName`, `contextKeyNamespace`\n30: \n31: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Define constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n32:   - Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL` (8h), `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` (15m), label/annotation keys\n33: \n34: ### Phase 2: Infrastructure Components\n35: \n36: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `sandboxCreator` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go`\n37:   - Fields: `k8sClient`, `sandboxController`, `storeClient`, `publicKey`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `createSandbox()` method for `sandboxCreator`\n40:   - Steps: register watcher → store placeholder → create CR → wait (2min) → resolve IP → update store\n41:   - Rollback on failure: delete CR + delete store entry\n42:   - Use independent 30s timeout context for rollback delete\n43: \n44: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `resolvePodIP()` method in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n45:   - Priority: sandbox name → annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` → informer cache → label selector\n46:   - Require PodRunning phase and non-empty PodIP\n47: \n48: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `buildEntryPoints()` function in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n49:   - Input: podIP, []TargetPort\n50:   - Output: []SandboxEntryPoint with format `host:port`\n51: \n52: ### Phase 3: Workload Builders\n53: \n54: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `buildSandboxObject()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n55:   - Input: *AgentRuntime, sessionID\n56:   - Name format: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n57:   - Set labels: session-id, workload-name, sandbox-name, managed-by\n58:   - Set annotations: idle-timeout\n59:   - Copy podTemplate from runtime.Spec.Template\n60:   - Set replicas=1, lifecycle.shutdownTime=now+MaxSessionDuration\n61: \n62: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `buildSandboxClaimObject()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n63:   - For CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0\n64:   - Minimal metadata, no full PodSpec\n65:   - APIVersion: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, Kind: `SandboxClaim`\n66: \n67: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement AuthMode injection for CodeInterpreter\n68:   - If AuthMode=picod and publicKey available: inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n69:   - Support optional fields: Command, Args, Environment, Resources, RuntimeClassName, ImagePullPolicy, ImagePullSecrets\n70: \n71: ### Phase 4: HTTP Handlers\n72: \n73: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `handleAgentRuntimeCreate()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agent_runtime.go`\n74:   - Parse JSON → set Kind=AgentRuntime → Validate()\n75:   - Get AgentRuntime from informer lister\n76:   - Check podTemplate non-nil\n77:   - Call createSandbox()\n78:   - Return CreateSandboxResponse (200) or error\n79: \n80: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `handleCodeInterpreterCreate()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/code_interpreter.go`\n81:   - Similar to AgentRuntime but:\n82:   - Kind=CodeInterpreter\n83:   - Support WarmPoolSize > 0 → buildSandboxClaimObject()\n84:   - Support AuthMode (picod/none)\n85:   - Default ports: [{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}] if spec.Ports empty\n86: \n87: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Register routes in `pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go`\n88:   - POST /v1/agent-runtime → handleAgentRuntimeCreate\n89:   - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId → handleDeleteSandbox\n90:   - POST /v1/code-interpreter → handleCodeInterpreterCreate\n91:   - DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId → handleDeleteSandbox\n92: \n93: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `handleDeleteSandbox()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agent_runtime.go`\n94:   - Load session from store by sessionId\n95:   - NotFound → 404 with message `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`\n96:   - Delete SandboxClaim if Kind=SandboxClaim, else delete Sandbox\n97:   - API NotFound on delete → treat as success\n98:   - DeleteSandboxBySessionID from store\n99:   - Return 200 `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}`\n100: \n101: ### Phase 5: Error Handling\n102: \n103: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Define error constants in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go` or `pkg/workloadmanager/response/response.go`\n104:   - ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound, ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound, ErrTemplateMissing, ErrPublicKeyMissing\n105: \n106: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement error mapping in handlers\n107:   - JSON bind失败 → 400 `Invalid request body`\n108:   - Validate 失败 → 400 `<field> is required`\n109:   - Template missing → 400 with `pod template` in message\n110:   - NotFound from informer → 404 `agent runtime not found` / `code interpreter not found`\n111:   - Auth失败 → 401 from authMiddleware\n112:   - Timeout/internal → 500 `internal server error`\n113: \n114: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement rollback strategy in `createSandbox()`\n115:   - CR 创建前失败: delete store placeholder\n116:   - CR 创建后超时: delete CR (30s timeout) + delete store\n117:   - Pod IP 解析失败: delete CR + delete store\n118:   - Store 更新失败: log warning, CR left for GC\n119: \n120: ### Phase 6: Integration\n121: \n122: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Integrate with `client-go` typed clients\n123:   - Use `AgentRuntimeInterface` and `CodeInterpreterInterface` for reading templates\n124:   - Use informers + listers for cached reads\n125: \n126: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Integrate with dynamic client\n127:   - Create Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs using `dynamic.Interface`\n128:   - GVR: `SandboxGVR`, `SandboxClaimGVR`\n129: \n130: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Integrate with SandboxReconciler\n131:   - Call `WatchSandboxOnce(ns, name)` before CR creation\n132:   - Wait on channel with 2min timeout\n133:   - Receive notification when status=running\n134: \n135: - [ ] **TASK-053**: Integrate with Store\n136:   - StoreSandbox() with placeholder before CR create\n137:   - UpdateSandbox() with full info after IP resolution\n138:   - DeleteSandboxBySessionID() on rollback or delete\n139: \n140: - [ ] **TASK-054**: Integrate with authMiddleware\n141:   - When EnableAuth=true: use per-user dynamic client from `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient`\n142:   - Cache key: `<namespace>:<serviceAccountName>`\n143: \n144: ### Phase 7: Testing (TDD)\n145: \n146: #### Unit Tests\n147: \n148: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestCreateSandboxRequest_Validate` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_test.go`\n149:   - Valid request → no error\n150:   - Empty name → error contains `name is required`\n151:   - Empty namespace → error contains `namespace is required`\n152:   - Invalid kind → error contains `kind is required`\n153: \n154: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Success` (TestCase-WM-001)\n155:   - Given: valid AgentRuntime in informer cache\n156:   - When: POST /v1/agent-runtime with valid JSON\n157:   - Then: 200, response contains sessionId and entryPoints\n158:   - Use fake clientset + mock store + mock SandboxReconciler\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Idempotent` (TestCase-WM-002)\n161:   - Given: two consecutive requests with same name\n162:   - When: first creation succeeds\n163:   - Then: second returns same sessionId\n164: \n165: - [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_MissingPodTemplate` (TestCase-WM-003)\n166:   - Given: AgentRuntime with spec.podTemplate=nil\n167:   - When: POST /v1/agent-runtime\n168:   - Then: 400, message contains `pod template`\n169: \n170: - [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_WarmPool`\n171:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0\n172:   - When: POST /v1/code-interpreter\n173:   - Then: creates SandboxClaim, response Kind=SandboxClaim\n174: \n175: - [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_DefaultPorts`\n176:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with empty spec.Ports\n177:   - When: creation succeeds\n178:   - Then: entryPoints contains default 8080/HTTP\n179: \n180: - [ ] **TEST-007**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_AuthModePicoD`\n181:   - Given: AuthMode=picod and publicKey available\n182:   - When: sandbox created\n183:   - Then: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env var injected\n184: \n185: - [ ] **TEST-008**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_AuthModeNone`\n186:   - Given: AuthMode=none\n187:   - When: sandbox created\n188:   - Then: no PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env var\n189: \n190: - [ ] **TEST-009**: `TestCreateSandbox_Timeout`\n191:   - Given: no running notification within 2min\n192:   - When: createSandbox() waits\n193:   - Then: error `sandbox creation timed out`, CR deleted, store entry deleted\n194: \n195: - [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestCreateSandbox_RollbackOnIPResolutionFailure`\n196:   - Given: pod IP resolution fails\n197:   - When: createSandbox() attempts to resolve\n198:   - Then: CR deleted, store entry deleted, error returned\n199: \n200: - [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestResolvePodIP_FromAnnotation`\n201:   - Given: Sandbox with annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name`\n202:   - When: resolvePodIP() called\n203:   - Then: uses annotated pod name\n204: \n205: - [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestResolvePodIP_FromOwnerReference`\n206:   - Given: pods listed by label, one has owner reference Kind=Sandbox\n207:   - When: resolvePodIP() called\n208:   - Then: selects pod with matching owner reference\n209: \n210: - [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestResolvePodIP_PodNotRunning`\n211:   - Given: pod in Pending/Failed phase\n212:   - When: resolvePodIP() called\n213:   - Then: error indicating pod not running\n214: \n215: - [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestBuildSandboxObject_LabelsAndAnnotations`\n216:   - Given: AgentRuntime with sessionTimeout\n217:   - When: buildSandboxObject() called\n218:   - Then: labels and annotations set correctly\n219: \n220: - [ ] **TEST-015**: `TestBuildSandboxClaimObject_MinimalMetadata`\n221:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0\n222:   - When: buildSandboxClaimObject() called\n223:   - Then: minimal metadata, no PodSpec\n224: \n225: - [ ] **TEST-016**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_Success`\n226:   - Given: session exists in store\n227:   - When: DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId\n228:   - Then: 200, CR deleted, store entry deleted\n229: \n230: - [ ] **TEST-017**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_NotFound` (Spec requirement)\n231:   - Given: no session key in store\n232:   - When: DELETE invoked\n233:   - Then: 404, message contains session id\n234: \n235: #### Test Infrastructure\n236: \n237: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `testEnv` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go`\n238:   - Fields: k8sClient, reconciler, store, server, redis (miniredis), fakeClient, dynamicClient\n239: \n240: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Implement `newTestEnv(t *testing.T)` function\n241:   - Start miniredis\n242:   - Create fake clientset with registered AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter\n243:   - Create fake dynamic client\n244:   - Initialize K8sClient, SandboxReconciler, Store\n245:   - Build Server (auth/TLS disabled)\n246: \n247: - [ ] **TEST-022**: Create mock implementations\n248:   - MockWorkloadManager interface\n249:   - Mock SandboxReconciler.WatchSandboxOnce returning controllable channel\n250: \n251: #### Integration Tests\n252: \n253: - [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestE2E_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox`\n254:   - Deploy AgentCube (Helm install to Kind cluster)\n255:   - Create ServiceAccount and get token\n256:   - POST /v1/agent-runtime\n257:   - Verify response contains sessionId and entryPoints\n258:   - Access sandbox via entryPoint to verify connectivity\n259:   - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId to cleanup\n260: \n261: - [ ] **TEST-031**: E2E fixture `echo_agent.yaml`\n262:   - Simple echo server AgentRuntime definition\n263: \n264: #### Coverage Verification\n265: \n266: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Run coverage check\n267:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n268:   - Verify test code / business code ratio > 0.4\n269:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n270: \n271: ### Phase 8: Documentation\n272: \n273: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add API examples to handler doc comments\n274:   - Example request/response for POST /v1/agent-runtime\n275:   - Example request/response for POST /v1/code-interpreter\n276: \n277: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Document error scenarios in handler doc comments\n278:   - List all HTTP status codes and conditions\n279: \n280: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Update pkg/workloadmanager/README.md\n281:   - Architecture diagram\n282:   - Component interaction flow\n283:   - Configuration options\n284: \n285: ## Acceptance Criteria\n286: \n287: - [ ] All handlers implemented and registered\n288: - [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n289: - [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.4\n290: - [ ] Error handling covers all spec-defined scenarios\n291: - [ ] Rollback strategy verified by tests\n292: - [ ] Integration with client-go, informers, dynamic client, Store, SandboxReconciler complete\n293: - [ ] Auth mode (EnableAuth) tested with per-user client cache\n294: - [ ] WarmPool support for CodeInterpreter verified\n295: - [ ] Timeout (2min) and rollback (30s) enforced\n296: - [ ] Pod IP resolution covers all paths (annotation, owner reference, label selector)\n297: \n298: ## Dependencies\n299: \n300: - **Completed**: ST-1 (CRD schemas), ST-2 (HTTP framework, auth middleware, informers)\n301: - **Required**: client-go typed clients, informers, listers operational\n302: - **Required**: SandboxReconciler operational (from controller package)\n303: - **Required**: Store interface (Redis-backed) operational\n\n(End of file - total 303 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `CreateSandboxRequest` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n  - Fields: `Kind`, `Name`, `Namespace` (all string)\n  - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n  - Validation rules: Kind ∈ {AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter}, Namespace non-empty, Name non-empty","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775859049486,"end":1775859049521}}}}
