{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859116092,"sessionID":"ses_2868da312ffeM3OfRVFAF4u2oG","part":{"id":"prt_d7972caaa001CAIA2IwXH5gVHo","messageID":"msg_d7972c194001mKfmDw9uxgwTXi","sessionID":"ses_2868da312ffeM3OfRVFAF4u2oG","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_1e3723d5cf1541f8aa07bcbf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md","content":"# AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-015 — PicoD Command Execution API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Core Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `ResourceLimits` struct in `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n  - Fields: `Timeout` (time.Duration), `MaxCPU` (float64), `MaxMemory` (int64), `MaxOutputSize` (int64), `MaxProcesses` (int)\n  - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n  - Validation rules: Timeout > 0, MaxCPU >= 0, MaxMemory > 0, MaxOutputSize > 0, MaxProcesses > 0\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `DefaultResourceLimits()` function in `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n  - Returns: Timeout=30s, MaxCPU=1.0, MaxMemory=128MiB, MaxOutputSize=10MiB, MaxProcesses=10\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `SecurityOptions` struct in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n  - Fields: `UID` (int), `GID` (int), `Capabilities` ([]string), `ReadOnlyFS` (bool), `NoNetwork` (bool), `AllowedCommands` ([]string)\n  - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `DefaultSecurityOpts()` function in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n  - Returns: UID/GID=-1 (no change), Capabilities=nil, ReadOnlyFS=false, NoNetwork=true, AllowedCommands=nil\n\n- [ ] **TASK-005**: Define `Command` struct in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n  - Fields: `Path` (string), `Args` ([]string), `Env` ([]string), `Dir` (string), `Stdin` (io.Reader), `Stdout` (io.Writer), `Stderr` (io.Writer)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-006**: Define `CommandResult` struct in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n  - Fields: `ExitCode` (int), `Stdout` ([]byte), `Stderr` ([]byte), `Duration` (time.Duration), `OOMKilled` (bool), `Timeout` (bool)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-007**: Define `ExecutionErrorType` and error constants in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n  - Types: `ExecutionErrorTimeout`, `ExecutionErrorOOM`, `ExecutionErrorCancelled`, `ExecutionErrorSecurity`, `ExecutionErrorResource`, `ExecutionErrorExec`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-008**: Define `ExecutionError` struct in `pkg/picod/errors.go`\n  - Fields: `Type` (ExecutionErrorType), `Message` (string), `Underlying` (error)\n  - Methods: `Error()`, `Unwrap()`\n\n### Phase 2: PicoD Core Implementation\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Define `PicoD` struct in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n  - Fields: `sandboxID` (string), `workDir` (string), `limits` (*ResourceLimits), `securityOpts` (*SecurityOptions), `logger` (klog.Logger)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Define `Option` type and functional options in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n  - Options: `WithWorkDir()`, `WithLimits()`, `WithSecurityOpts()`, `WithLogger()`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `New()` function in `pkg/picod/picod.go`\n  - Creates PicoD with defaults, applies options\n  - Default workDir: `/tmp/picod/{sandboxID}`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `Config` struct and `LoadConfig()` in `pkg/picod/config.go`\n  - Loads from environment variables: PICOD_WORKDIR, PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT, PICOD_MAX_MEMORY, PICOD_MAX_CPU, PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE, PICOD_MAX_PROCESSES\n  - Applies defaults when env vars not set\n\n### Phase 3: Command Execution\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `Run()` method in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n  - Flow: ValidateCommand → Create exec.Cmd → Apply resource limits → Capture output → Start → Wait → Build result\n  - Handle timeout, OOM, cancellation detection\n  - Return *CommandResult and error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `Start()` method in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n  - Starts command without waiting\n  - Returns *Process\n\n- [ ] **TASK-022**: Define `Process` struct in `pkg/picod/process.go`\n  - Fields: `PID` (int), `cmd` (*exec.Cmd), `startTime` (time.Time)\n  - Methods: `Wait()`, `Kill()`, `Signal()`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `Wait()` method for Process\n  - Waits for process completion\n  - Builds and returns CommandResult\n\n- [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `Kill()` and `Signal()` methods for Process\n  - Sends signals to process\n\n### Phase 4: Resource Limit Enforcement\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `Apply()` method for ResourceLimits in `pkg/picod/limits.go`\n  - Applies memory limits via syscall.Setrlimit (RLIMIT_AS)\n  - Applies process limits via syscall.Setrlimit (RLIMIT_NPROC)\n  - Configures cmd.SysProcAttr for process group\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement CPU limit enforcement logic\n  - Use cgroups for CPU limits (Linux-specific)\n  - Fallback gracefully on non-Linux platforms\n\n### Phase 5: Security Validation\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `ValidateCommand()` function in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n  - Checks command against AllowedCommands allowlist\n  - Validates working directory is within workspace\n  - Checks for path traversal in arguments\n  - Validates environment variables (blocks LD_PRELOAD, LD_LIBRARY_PATH)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `IsPathSafe()` function in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n  - Checks if path is within allowed workspace using filepath.Abs and strings.HasPrefix\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `DropPrivileges()` function in `pkg/picod/security.go`\n  - Drops privileges to specified UID/GID using syscall.Setuid/Setgid\n\n### Phase 6: Output Handling\n\n- [ ] **TASK-050**: Define `OutputHandler` interface in `pkg/picod/output.go`\n  - Methods: `OnStdout([]byte)`, `OnStderr([]byte)`, `OnComplete(*CommandResult)`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `RunWithStreaming()` method in `pkg/picod/executor.go`\n  - Executes command with streaming output\n  - Calls handler callbacks as data becomes available\n\n### Phase 7: Unit Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: Create `TestResourceLimits_Validate` in `pkg/picod/limits_test.go`\n  - Valid limits → no error\n  - Timeout=0 → error\n  - MaxMemory<=0 → error\n  - MaxOutputSize<=0 → error\n  - MaxProcesses<=0 → error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: Create `TestSecurityOptions_Validate` in `pkg/picod/security_test.go`\n  - Valid options → no error\n  - Invalid UID/GID → error\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: Create `TestPicoD_New` in `pkg/picod/picod_test.go`\n  - Default initialization\n  - WithWorkDir option\n  - WithLimits option\n  - WithSecurityOpts option\n  - WithLogger option\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: Create `TestPicoD_Run_Success` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n  - Execute simple command (echo)\n  - Verify ExitCode=0, Stdout captured\n\n- [ ] **TEST-005**: Create `TestPicoD_Run_Timeout` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n  - Command exceeds timeout\n  - Verify Timeout=true in result\n  - Verify ExecutionErrorTimeout returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-006**: Create `TestPicoD_Run_Cancelled` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n  - Context cancelled before command completes\n  - Verify ExecutionErrorCancelled returned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-007**: Create `TestPicoD_OutputCapture` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n  - Capture stdout and stderr\n  - Verify correct output in CommandResult\n\n- [ ] **TEST-008**: Create `TestPicoD_SecurityValidation` in `pkg/picod/executor_test.go`\n  - Command not in allowlist → ExecutionErrorSecurity\n  - Path traversal in args → ExecutionErrorSecurity\n  - Dangerous env var → ExecutionErrorSecurity\n\n- [ ] **TEST-009**: Create `TestPicoD_ExecutionErrorTypes` in `pkg/picod/errors_test.go`\n  - Verify error type classification\n  - Verify Error() and Unwrap() work correctly\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: Create `TestProcess_Wait` in `pkg/picod/process_test.go`\n  - Start process, wait for completion\n  - Verify CommandResult built correctly\n\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: Create `TestProcess_Kill` in `pkg/picod/process_test.go`\n  - Start process, send kill signal\n  - Verify process terminated\n\n- [ ] **TEST-012**: Create `TestLoadConfig` in `pkg/picod/config_test.go`\n  - Load from environment variables\n  - Verify defaults applied when env vars not set\n\n- [ ] **TEST-013**: Create `TestIsPathSafe` in `pkg/picod/security_test.go`\n  - Safe paths → true\n  - Path traversal → false\n  - Absolute path outside workspace → false\n\n- [ ] **TEST-014**: Create `TestRunWithStreaming` in `pkg/picod/output_test.go`\n  - Streaming output captured via handler\n  - Verify OnStdout/OnStderr/OnComplete called\n\n### Phase 8: Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `TestPicoD_Integration_FullLifecycle` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n  - Full execution flow with real commands\n  - Verify end-to-end functionality\n\n- [ ] **TEST-021**: Create `TestPicoD_Integration_Concurrent` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n  - Execute multiple commands concurrently\n  - Verify isolation and correct results\n\n- [ ] **TEST-022**: Create `TestPicoD_Integration_ResourceLimits` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n  - Create memory-intensive command\n  - Verify OOM killed when exceeds limit\n\n- [ ] **TEST-023**: Create `TestPicoD_Integration_Streaming` in `pkg/picod/integration_test.go`\n  - Long-running command with streaming output\n  - Verify handler receives all output\n\n### Phase 9: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add Go doc comments to all public types and functions\n  - Include usage examples in doc comments\n\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Create `pkg/picod/README.md`\n  - Architecture overview\n  - Usage examples\n  - Configuration options\n  - Error handling guide\n\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Add API examples to handler doc comments\n  - Example: creating PicoD instance\n  - Example: running command\n  - Example: streaming output\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] PicoD struct implements all required methods\n- [ ] Resource limits enforced (timeout, CPU, memory, output size)\n- [ ] Output capture works correctly (stdout, stderr, exit code)\n- [ ] Cancellation via context is supported\n- [ ] Security validations prevent dangerous operations\n- [ ] Streaming output is supported\n- [ ] All unit tests pass\n- [ ] Integration tests pass\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80%\n- [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n- [ ] Error types properly classified and documented\n- [ ] Each .go file has corresponding _test.go file\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Status |\n|------------|--------|\n| Go 1.21+ | Required |\n| k8s.io/klog/v2 | Required |\n| context package | Required |\n| os/exec package | Required |\n| syscall package | Required |\n| AR-012 (Sandbox Infrastructure) | Completed |\n| AR-013 (Session Storage) | Completed |\n| AR-014 (Valkey Storage) | Completed |\n\n## Test Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] **TEST-030**: Create `testEnv` struct for unit tests\n  - Mock logger\n  - Temporary test directories\n\n- [ ] **TEST-031**: Create mock OutputHandler for testing\n  - Track OnStdout/OnStderr/OnComplete calls\n\n## Coverage Verification\n\n- [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n  - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/picod/... ./pkg/picod/...`\n  - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n  - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775859116079,"end":1775859116089}}}}
